criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Patient aged 18 or more;

          -  Patient whose medical care requires a peripheral venous catheter;

          -  Insertion of the peripheral venous catheter on the upper limb.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Patient clinically unstable;

          -  Patient incapable of discernment or with whom it is difficult to communicate (altered
             mental status, intoxication, alcoholized patient, insufficient French notions to give
             an informed consent and answer questions about pain and anxiety, hearing-impaired
             patient);

          -  Patient unable to correctly use the rulers (e.g. visually impaired patient);

          -  Impaired upper limb (e.g. lymphedema);

          -  Patient incarcerated;

          -  Patient transferred from another hospital;

          -  Patient who has already taken part in the study;

          -  Patient who knows beforehand that communication will be evaluated;

          -  Patient, caregiver or investigator who knows beforehand which message will be
             delivered (first phase of the study).
